The paper presents new algorithms for the $(\Delta+1)$-coloring problem in three different models of computation: distributed computing, massively parallel computation, and centralized local computation. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
